Beijing: China Minzu University Press.Mongi, Mòqí 莫其, or mo21 ndʑi21 (autonym), is a Lolo-Burmese language with about 50,000 speakers in Wuding, Luquan, Songming, Kunming, Mile, and other counties of Yunnan. Chen (2010) classifies it as a Nasu (Eastern Yi) dialect.
